# Testing rules

See `docs/TESTING.md` and `docs/AI_DEVELOPMENT_GUARDRAILS.md`.

## Smoke tier (protected, <60s)

`test_runner.gd --tier=smoke` runs only:

- `race_quick_smoke_test.gd`
- `map_selection_test.gd`

Do **not** add slow tests to `SMOKE_TESTS`.

## Tier selection

| Task | Tier |
|------|------|
| Small isolated code | smoke |
| Race lifecycle | smoke + core |
| Finish / OOB / zombie authority | smoke + core |
| Map / catalog / controller | smoke + certification |
| Bridge gameplay | + map tier |

## Certification

- `map_certification_test.gd` — City Highway + Broken Bridge TEST
- Invalid map id and missing `CoreRoad` must fail loudly
- Do not disable guards to green tests

## Anti-patterns

- Ignoring `MAP LOAD FAILED` or `MAP CERTIFICATION FAILED` in output.
- Treating City Highway load as success when another map was requested.
- Adding `race_lifecycle_smoke_test` or bridge gameplay to smoke.

## Commands

```bash
godot --headless --path . -s res://scripts/debug/test_runner.gd -- --tier=smoke
godot --headless --path . -s res://scripts/debug/test_runner.gd -- --tier=core
godot --headless --path . -s res://scripts/debug/test_runner.gd -- --tier=certification
```
